obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (33968)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33968&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Indian Christian Marriage Act, 1872.`
  line
  line `Extent.^1[It extends to the whole of India ^2[except ^3[the territories which, immediately before the`
  line `1st November, 1956, were comprised in the States] of Travancore-Cochin, Manipur and ^4***].]^5`
  line
  line ^6*****
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O. 1950 for the second para., as amended by A. O. 1937 and A.O. 1948: [NOTE: The Act does not extend to the`
  line `State of Manipur, vide Act 30 of 1950, s. 3(2A) and Sch. As amended by Act 68 of 1956, s. 2. The Act has been extended to`
  line `and brought into force in Dadra and Nagar Haveli (w.e.f. 1-7-1965) by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and Sch. I.]`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for "except Part B States".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Adaption of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "the States".`
  line
  line `4. The words "State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10- 2019). .`
  line
  line `5. In its application to Pondicherry, in section 1, the following proviso shall be added at the end of section 1`
  line
  line `"Provided that nothing contained in this Act shall apply to the Renoncants of the Union territory of Pondicherry."--`
  line
  line `(vide Act 26 of 1968).`
  line
  line `6. The commencement cl. rep. by Act 16 of 1874, s. 1 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (33969)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Enactments repealed.]—Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1938 (1 of 1938), s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33969&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (33970)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33970&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,--
  line
  line `"Church of England" "Anglican".--mean and apply to the Church of England as by law`
  line established;
  line
  line `"Church of Scotland".--means the Church of Scotland as by law established;`
  line
  line `"Church of Rome" "Roman Catholic".--mean and apply to the Church which regards the Pope of`
  line `Rome as its spiritual head;`
  line
  line `"Church".--includes any chapel or other building generally used for public Christian worship;`
  line
  line `^1["India".--means the ^2[territories] to which this Act extends;]`
  line
  line `"minor".--minor means a person who has not completed the age of twenty-one years and who is`
  line `not a widower or a widow;`
  line
  line ^3*****
  line
  line `"Christians".--the expression "Christians" means persons professing the Christian religion;`
  line
  line `"Indian Christians".--^4[and the expression "Indian Christians" includes the Christian descendants of`
  line `natives of India converted to Christianity, as well as such converts;]`
  line
  line `^5["Registrar General of Births, Deaths and Marriages".--means a Registrar General of Births,Deaths and Marriages appointed under the Births, Deaths and Marriages Registration Act, 1886`
  line `(6 of 1886).]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "territory comprised in the States".`
  line
  line `3. The definition of "Native State" omitted. by the A. O. 1937.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by A. O. 1950, for the definition.`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (33971)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Marriages to be solemnized according to Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the Second Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33971&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Every marriage between persons, one or both of`
  line `whom is ^1[or are] a Christian or Christians, shall be solemnized in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `next following section; and any such marriage solemnized otherwise than in accordance with such`
  line `provisions shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (33972)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Persons by whom marriages may be solemnized.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33972&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Marriages may be solemnized in ^1[India]--`
  line
  line `(1) by any person who has received episcopal ordination, provided that the marriage be solemnized`
  line `according to the rules, rites, ceremonies and customs of the Church of which he is a Minister;`
  line
  line `(2) by any Clergyman of the Church of Scotland, provided that such marriage be solemnized`
  line `according to the rules, rites, ceremonies and customs of the Church of Scotland;`
  line
  line `(3) by any Minister of Religion licensed under this Act to solemnize marriages;`
  line
  line `(4) by, or in the presence of, a Marriage Registrar appointed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(5) by any person licensed under this Act to grant certificates of marriage between ^2[Indian`
  line Christians].
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for "Part A States and Part C States".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "Native Christians".`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (33973)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Grant and revocation of licenses to solemnize marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33973&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[Grant and revocation of licenses to solemnize marriages.--The State Government, so far as`
  line `regards the territories under its administration, ^2*** may, by notification in the Official Gazette ^3** *,`
  line `grant licenses to Ministers of Religion to solemnize marriages within such territories ^4* * * and may, by a`
  line `a like notification revoke such licenses.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1891, s. 1, for s. 6.`
  line
  line `2. The words "and the Central Government, so far as regards any Indian State" omitted by the A. O. 1950.`
  line
  line `3. The words "or in the Gazette of India, as the case may be" omitted by the A. O. 1937.`
  line
  line `4. The words "and State, respectively," omitted by the A. O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (33974)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Marriage Registrars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33974&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may appoint one or more Christians, either by`
  line `name or as holding any office for the time being, to be the Marriage Registrar or Marriage Registrars for`
  line `any district subject to its administration.`
  line
  line `Senior Marriage Registrar.Where there are more Marriage Registrars than one in any district, the`
  line `State Government shall appoint one of them to be the Senior Marriage Registrar.`
  line
  line `Magistrate when to be Marriage Registrar.When there is only one Marriage Registrar in a`
  line `district, and such Registrar is absent from such district, or ill, or when his office is temporarily vacant, the`
  line `Magistrate of the district shall act as, and be, Marriage Registrar thereof during such absence, illness, or`
  line `temporary vacancy.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line KARNATAKA
  line
  line `In section 7, for the words, "Magistrate of the district" the words "District Magistrate" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 13 of 1965, s. 67 and Schedule]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (33975)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Marriage Registrars in Indian States.]—Omitted by the A. O. 1950.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33975&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (33976)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Licensing of persons to grant certificates of marriage between Indian Christians.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33976&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The State`
  line `Government ^2* * * may grant a license to any Christian, either by name or as holding any office for the`
  line `time being, authorizing him to grant certificates of marriage between ^1[Indian] Christians.`
  line
  line `Any such license may be revoked by the authority by which it was granted, and every such grant or`
  line `revocation shall be notified in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for “Part A States and Part C States”.`
  line
  line `2. The words and brackets "or (so far as regard any Indian State) the Central Government" omitted by the A. O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (33977)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Time for solemnizing marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1891, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33977&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every marriage under this Act shall be solemnized between`
  line `the hours of six in the morning and seven in the evening:`
  line
  line `Exceptions.Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(1) a Clergyman of the Church of England solemnizing a marriage under a special license permitting`
  line `him to do so at any hour other than between six in the morning and seven in the evening, under the hand`
  line `and seal of the Anglican Bishop of the Diocese or his Commissary, or`
  line
  line `(2) a Clergyman of the Church of Rome solemnizing a marriage between the hours of seven in the`
  line `evening and six in the morning, when he has received a general or special license in that behalf from the`
  line `Roman Catholic Bishop of the Diocese or Vicariate in which such marriage is so solemnized, or from`
  line `such person as the same Bishop has authorized to grant such license, ^1[or`
  line
  line `(3) a Clergyman of the Church of Scotland solemnizing a marriage according to the rules, rites,`
  line `ceremonies and customs of the Church of Scotland.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (33978)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Place for solemnizing marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33978&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No Clergyman of the Church of England shall solemnize a`
  line `marriage in any place other than a church ^1[where worship is generally held according to the forms of the`
  line `Church of England],`
  line
  line `unless there is no ^1[such] church within five miles distance by the shortest road from isuch place, or`
  line
  line `unless he has received a special license, authorizing him to do so under the hand and seal of the`
  line `Anglican Bishop of the Diocese or his Commissary.`
  line
  line `Fee for special license.—For such special license, the Registrar of the Diocese may charge such`
  line `additional fee as the said Bishop from time to time authorizes.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (33979)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Notice of intended marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33979&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a marriage is intended to be solemnized by a Minister`
  line `of Religion licensed to solemnize marriages under this Act—`
  line
  line `one of the persons intending marriage shall give notice in writing, according to the form contained in`
  line `the First Schedule hereto annexed, or to the like effect, to the Minister of Religion whom he or she desires`
  line `to solemnize the marriage, and shall state therein—`
  line
  line `(a) the name and surname, and the profession or condition, of each of the persons intending`
  line marriage,
  line
  line `(b) the dwelling-place of each of them,`
  line
  line `(c) the time during which each has dwelt there, and`
  line
  line `(d) the church or private dwelling in which the marriage is to be solemnized:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if either of such persons has dwelt in the place mentioned in the notice during more`
  line `than one month, it may be stated therein that he or she has dwelt there one month and upwards.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (33980)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Publication of such notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33980&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `If the persons intending marriage desire it to be solemnized in a`
  line `particular church, and if the Minister of Religion to whom such notice has been delivered be entitled to`
  line `officiate therein, he shall cause the notice to be affixed in some conspicuous part of such church.`
  line
  line `Return or transfer of notice.—But if he is not entitled to officiate as a Minister in such church, he`
  line `shall, at his option, either return the notice, to the person who delivered it to him, or deliver it to some`
  line `other Minister entitled to officiate therein, who shall thereupon cause the notice to be affixed as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (33981)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Notice of intended marriage in private dwelling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33981&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If it be intended that the marriage shall be`
  line `solemnized in a private dwelling, the Minister of Religion, on receiving the notice prescribed in`
  line `section 12, shall forward it to the Marriage Registrar of the district, who shall affix the same to some`
  line `conspicuous place in his own office.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (33982)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Sending copy of notice to Marriage Registrar when one party is a minor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33982&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `When one of the`
  line `persons intending marriage is a minor, every Minister receiving such notice shall, unless within`
  line `twenty-four hours after its receipt he returns the same under the provisions of section 13, send by the post`
  line `or otherwise a copy of such notice to the Marriage Registrar of the district, or, if there be more than one`
  line `Registrar of such district, to the Senior Marriage Registrar.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (33983)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Procedure on receipt of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33983&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Marriage Registrar or Senior Marriage Registrar, as the`
  line `case may be, on receiving any such notice, shall affix it to some conspicuous place in his own office, and`
  line `the latter shall further cause a copy of the said notice to be sent to each of the other Marriage Registrars in`
  line `the same district, who shall likewise publish the same in the manner above directed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (33984)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Issue of certificate of notice given and declaration made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33984&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any Minister of Religion`
  line `consenting or intending to solemnize any such marriage as aforesaid, shall, on being required so to do by`
  line `or on behalf of the person by whom the notice was given, and upon one of the persons intending marriage`
  line `making the declaration hereinafter required, issue under his hand a certificate of such notice having been`
  line `given and of such declaration having been made:`
  line
  line Proviso.—Provided—
  line
  line `(1) that no such certificate shall be issued until the expiration of four days after the date of the receipt`
  line `of the notice by such Minister;`
  line
  line `(2) that no lawful impediment be shown to his satisfaction why such certificate should not issue; and`
  line
  line `(3) that the issue of such certificate has not been forbidden, in manner hereinafter mentioned, by any`
  line `person authorized in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (33985)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Declaration before issue of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33985&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The certificate mentioned in section 17 shall not be`
  line `issued until one of the persons intending marriage has appeared personally before the Minister and made`
  line `a solemn declaration—`
  line
  line `(a) that he or she believes that there is not any impediment of kindred or affinity, or other lawful`
  line `hindrance, to the said marriage,`
  line
  line `and when either or both of the parties is or are a minor or minors,`
  line
  line `(b) that the consent or consents required by law has or have been obtained thereto, or that there is`
  line `no person resident in India having authority to give such consent, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (33986)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Consent of father, or guardian, or mother.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33986&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The father, if living, of any minor, or, if the father`
  line `be dead. the guardian of the person of such minor, and, in case there be no such guardian, then the mother`
  line `of such minor, may give consent to the minor's marriage,`
  line
  line `and such consent is hereby required for the same marriage, unless no person authorized to give such`
  line `consent be resident in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (33987)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to prohibit by notice issue of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33987&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Every person whose consent to a marriage is`
  line `required under section 19, is hereby authorized to prohibit the issue of the certificate by any Minister, at`
  line `any time before the issue of the same, by notice in writing to such Minister, subscribed by the person so`
  line `authorized with his or her name and place of abode and position with respect to either of the persons`
  line `intending marriage, by reason of which he or she is so authorized as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (33988)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Procedure on receipt of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33988&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If any such notice be received by such Minister, he shall not`
  line `issue his certificate and shall not solemnize the said marriage until he has examined into the matter of the`
  line `said prohibition, and is satisfied that the person prohibiting the marriage has no lawful authority for such`
  line prohibition,
  line
  line `or until the said notice is withdrawn by the person who gave it.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (33989)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Issue of certificate in case of minority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33989&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `When either of the persons intending marriage is a`
  line `minor, and the Minister is not satisfied that the consent of the person whose consent to such marriage is`
  line `required by section 19 has been obtained, such Minister shall not issue such certificate until the expiration`
  line `of fourteen days after the receipt by him of the notice of marriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (33990)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Issue of certificates to Indian Christians.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "Native Christians".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33990&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `When any ^1[Indian Christians] about to be married`
  line `takes a notice of marriage to a Minister of Religion, or applies for a certificate from such Minister under`
  line `section 17, such Minister shall, before issuing the certificate, ascertain whether such ^1[Indian Christians]`
  line `is cognizant of the purport and effect of the said notice or certificate, as the case may be, and, if not, shall`
  line `translate or cause to be translated the notice or certificate to such ^1[Indian Christian] into some language`
  line `which he understands.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (33991)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Form of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33991&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The certificate to be issued by such Minister shall be in the form contained`
  line `in the Second Schedule hereto annexed, or to the like effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (33992)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Solemnization of marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33992&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `After the issue of the certificate by the Minister, marriage may be`
  line `solemnized between the persons therein described according to such form or ceremony as the Minister`
  line `thinks fit to adopt:`
  line
  line `Provided that the marriage be solemnized in the presence of at least two witnesses besides the`
  line Minister.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (33993)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Certificate void if marriage not solemnized within two months.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33993&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a marriage is not`
  line `solemnized within two months after the date of the certificate issued by such Minister as aforesaid, such`
  line `certificate and all proceedings (if any) thereon shall be void,`
  line
  line `and no person shall proceed to solemnize the said marriage until new notice has been given and a`
  line `certificate thereof issued in manner aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (33994)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Marriages when to be registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for "a Part A State or a Part C State".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33994&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `All marriages hereafter solemnized in ^1[India] between`
  line `persons one or both of whom professes or profess the Christian religion, except marriages solemnized`
  line `under Part V or Part VI of this Act, shall be registered in manner hereinafter prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (33995)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Registration of marriages solemnized by Clergymen of Church of England.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33995&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `Clergyman of the Church of England shall keep a register of marriages and shall register therein,`
  line `according to the tabular form set forth in the Third Schedule hereto annexed, every marriage which he`
  line `solemnizes under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (33996)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Quarterly returns to Archdeaconry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30, for "Secretary to the Local Government.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33996&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Every Clergyman of the Church of England shall send`
  line `four times in every year returns in duplicate, authenticated by his signature, of the entries in the register of`
  line `marriages solemnized at any place where he has any spiritual charge, to the Registrar of the Archdeaconry`
  line `to which he is subject, or within the limits of which such place is situate.`
  line
  line `Contents of returns.—Such quarterly returns shall contain all the entries of marriages contained in`
  line `the said register from the first day of January to the thirty-first day of March, from the first day of April,`
  line `to the thirtieth day of June, from the first day of July, to the thirtieth day of September, and from the first`
  line `day of October to the thirty-first day of December, of each year, respectively, and shall be sent by such`
  line `Clergyman, within two weeks from the expiration of each of the quarters above specified.`
  line
  line `The said Registrar upon receiving the said returns shall send one copy thereof to the ^1`
  line Registrar
  line `General of Births, Deaths and Marriages.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (33997)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Registration and returns of marriages solemnized by Clergymen of Church of Rome.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30, for "Secretary to the Local Government"..`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33997&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Every marriage solemnized by a Clergyman of the Church of Rome shall be registered by the person and according to the form directed in that behalf by the Roman Catholic Bishop of the Diocese or`
  line `Vicariate in which such marriage is solemnized,`
  line
  line `and such person shall forward quarterly to the ^1[Registrar General of Births, Deaths and Marriages]`
  line `returns of the entries of all marriages registered by him during the three months next preceding.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (33998)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Registration and returns of marriages solemnized by Clergymen of Church of Scotland.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30, for "Secretary to the Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33998&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Every Clergyman of the Church of Scotland shall keep a register of marriages,`
  line
  line `and shall register therein, according to the tabular form set forth in the Third Schedule hereto`
  line `annexed, every marriage which he solemnizes under this Act,`
  line
  line `and shall forward quarterly to the ^1[Registrar General of Births, Deaths and Marriages], through the`
  line `Senior Chaplain of the Church of Scotland, returns, similar to those prescribed in section 29, of all such`
  line marriages.
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (33999)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Certain marriages to be registered in duplicate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=33999&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every marriage solemnized by any person`
  line `who has received episcopal ordination, but who is not a Clergyman of the Church of England, or of the`
  line `Church of Rome, or by any Minister of Religion licensed under this Act to solemnize marriages, shall`
  line `immediately after the solemnization thereof, be registered in duplicate by the person solemnizing the`
  line `same; (that is to say) in a marriage-register book to be kept by him for that purpose, according to the form`
  line `contained in the Fourth Schedule hereto annexed, and also in a certificate attached to the`
  line `marriage-register-book as a counterfoil.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (34000)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Entries of such marriages to be signed and attested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34000&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The entry of such marriage in both the`
  line `certificate and marriage-register-book shall be signed by the person solemnizing the marriage, and also by`
  line `the persons married, and shall be attested by two credible witnesses, other than the person solemnizing`
  line `the marriage, present at its solemnization.`
  line
  line `Every such entry shall be made in order from the beginning to the end of the book, and the number of`
  line `the certificate shall correspond with that of the entry in the marriage-register-book.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (34001)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Certificate to be forwarded to Marriages Registrar, copied and sent to Registrar General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30, for "Secretary to the Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34001&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The person solemnizing the marriage shall forthwith separate the certificate from the`
  line `marriage-register-book and send it, within one month from the time of the solemnization, to the Marriage`
  line `Registrar of the district in which the marriage was solemnized, or, if there be more Marriage Registrars`
  line `than one, to the Senior Marriage Registrar,`
  line
  line `who shall cause such certificate to be copied into a book to be kept by him for that purpose,`
  line
  line `and shall send all the certificates which he has received during the month, with such number and`
  line `signature or initials added thereto as are hereinafter required, to the ^1[Registrar General of Births, Deaths`
  line `and Marriages.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (34002)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Copies of certificates to be entered and numbered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34002&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Such copies shall be entered in order from`
  line `the beginning to the end of the said book, and shall bear both the number of the certificate as copied, and`
  line `also a number to be entered by the Marriage Registrar, indicating the number of the entry of the said copy`
  line `in the said book, according to the order in which he receives each certificate.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (34003)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Registrar to add number of entry to certificate, and send to Registrar General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30, for “Secretary to the Local Government”.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34003&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Marriage Registrar shall also add such last-mentioned number of the entry of the copy in the book to the`
  line `certificate, with his signature or initials, and shall, at the end of every month, send the same to the`
  line `^1[Registrar General of Births, Deaths and Marriages.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (34004)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Registration of marriages between Indian Christians, by persons referred to in clauses (1), (2) and (3) of section 5.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34004&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `When any marriage between ^1[Indian Christians] is solemnized ^2[by any such`
  line `person, Clergyman or Minister of Religion as is referred to in clause (1), clause (2) or clause (3) of`
  line `section 5], the person solemnizing the same shall, instead of proceeding in the manner provided by`
  line `sections 28 to 36, both inclusive, register the marriage in a separate register-book, and shall keep it safely until it is filled, or, if he leave the district in which he solemnized the marriage before the said book is`
  line `filled, shall make over the same to the person succeeding to his duties in the said district.`
  line
  line `Custody and disposal of register-book.-- Whoever has the control of the book at the time when it is`
  line `filled, shall send it to the Marriage Registrar of the district, or, if there be more Marriage Registrars than`
  line `one, to the Senior Marriage Registrar, who shall send it to the ^3[Registrar General of Births, Deaths and`
  line `Marriages,] to be kept by him with the records of his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "Native Christians".`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1928, s. 2 and the first Schedule, for "under Part I or Part III or this Act".`
  line `3. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "Native Christians".`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (34005)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Notice of intended marriage before Marriage Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34005&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `When a marriage is intended to be`
  line `solemnized by, or in the presence of, a Marriage Registrar, one of the parties to such marriage shall give`
  line `notice in writing, in the form contained in the First Schedule hereto annexed, or to the like effect, to any`
  line `Marriage Registrar of the district within which the parties have dwelt,`
  line
  line `or, if the parties dwell in different districts, shall give the like notice to a Marriage Registrar of each`
  line district,
  line
  line `and shall state therein the name and surname, and the profession or condition, of each of the parties`
  line `intending marriage, the dwelling-place of each of them, the time during which each has dwelt therein, and`
  line `the place at which the marriage is to be solemnized:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if either party has dwelt in the place stated in the notice for more than one month, it`
  line `may be stated therein that he or she has dwelt there one month and upwards.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (34006)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Publication of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34006&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Every Marriage Registrar shall, on receiving any such notice, cause a`
  line `copy thereof to be affixed in some conspicuous place in his office.`
  line
  line `When one of the parties intending marriage is a minor, every Marriage Registrar shall, within twentyfour hours after the receipt by him of the notice of such marriage, send, by post or otherwise, a copy of`
  line `such notice to each of the other Marriage Registrars (if any) in the same district, who shall likewise affix`
  line `the copy in some conspicuous place in his own office.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (34007)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Notice to be filed and copy entered in Marriage Notice Book.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34007&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The Marriage Registrar shall`
  line `file all such notices and keep them with the records of his office,`
  line
  line `and shall also forthwith enter a true copy of all such notices in a book to be furnished to him for that`
  line `purpose by the State Government, and to be called the "Marriage Notice Book";`
  line
  line `and the Marriage Notice Book shall be open at all reasonable times, without fee, to all persons`
  line `desirous of inspecting the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (34008)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Certificate of notice given and oath made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34008&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `If the party by whom the notice was given requests`
  line `the Marriage Registrar to issue the certificate next hereinafter mentioned, and if one of the parties`
  line `intending marriage has made oath as hereinafter required, the Marriage Registrar shall issue under his`
  line `hand a certificate of such notice having been given and of such oath having been made:`
  line
  line `Proviso.-- Provided--`
  line
  line `that no lawful impediment be shown to his satisfaction why such certificate should not issue;`
  line
  line `that the issue of such certificate has not been forbidden, in manner hereinafter mentioned, by any`
  line `person authorized in that behalf by this Act;`
  line
  line `that four days after the receipt of the notice have expired, and further,`
  line
  line `that where, by such oath, it appears that one of the parties intending marriage is a minor, fourteen`
  line `days after the entry of such notice have expired.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (34009)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Oath before issue of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30, for "Secretary to the Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34009&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The certificate mentioned in section 41 shall not be issued by`
  line `any Marriage Registrar, until one of the parties intending marriage appears personally before such`
  line `Marriage Registrar, and makes oath^1`
  line
  line `(a) that he or she believes that there is not any impediment of kindred or affinity, or other lawful`
  line `hindrance, to the said marriage, and`
  line
  line `(b) that both the parties have, or (where they have dwelt in the districts of different Marriage`
  line `Registrars) that the party making such oath has, had their, his or her usual place of abode within the`
  line `district of such Marriage Registrar,`
  line
  line `and, where either or each of the parties is a minor,`
  line
  line `(c) that the consent or consents to such marriage required by law has or have been obtained`
  line `thereto, or that there is no person resident in India authorized to give such consent, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (34010)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Petition to High Court to order certificate in less than fourteen days.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34010&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `When one of the`
  line `parties intending marriage is a minor, and both such parties are at the time resident in any of the towns of`
  line `Calcutta, Madras and Bombay, and are desirous of being married in less than fourteen days after the entry`
  line `of such notice as aforesaid, they may apply by petition to a Judge of the High Court, for an order upon the`
  line `Marriage Registrar to whom the notice of marriage has been given, directing him to issue his certificate`
  line `before the expiration of the said fourteen days required by section 41.`
  line
  line `Order on petition.-- And on sufficient cause being shown, the said Judge may, in his discretion,`
  line `make an order upon such Marriage Registrar, directing him to issue his certificate at any time to be`
  line `mentioned in the said order before the expiration of the fourteen days so required.`
  line
  line `And the said Marriage Registrar, on receipt of the said order, shall issue his certificate in accordance`
  line therewith.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (34011)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Consent of father or guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34011&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 19 apply to every marriage under this`
  line `Part, either of the parties to which is a minor;`
  line
  line `Protest against issue of certificate.-- And any person whose consent to such marriage would be`
  line `required thereunder may enter a protest against the issue of the Marriage Registrar's certificate, by`
  line `writing, at any time before the issue of such certificate, the word "forbidden" opposite to the entry of the`
  line `notice of such intended marriage in the Marriage Notice Book, and by subscribing thereto his or her name`
  line `and place of abode, and his or her position with respect to either of the parties, by reason of which he or`
  line `she is so authorized.`
  line
  line `Effect of protest.-- When such protest has been entered, no certificate shall issue until the Marriage`
  line `Registrar has examined into the matter of the protest, and is satisfied that it ought not to obstruct the issue`
  line `of the certificate for the said marriage, or until the protest be withdrawn by the person who entered it.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (34012)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Petition where person whose consent is necessary is insane, or unjustly withholds consent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34012&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `If any person whose consent is necessary to any marriage under this Part is of unsound mind,`
  line
  line `or if any such person (other than the father) without just cause withholds his consent to the marriage,`
  line
  line `the parties intending marriage may apply by petition, where the person whose consent is necessary is`
  line `resident within any of the towns of Calcutta, Madras and Bombay, to a Judge of the High Court, or if he`
  line `is not resident within any of the said towns, then to the District Judge.`
  line
  line `Procedure on petition.-- And the said Judge of the High Court, or District Judge, as the case may be,`
  line `may examine the allegations of the petition in a summary way;`
  line
  line `and, if upon examination such marriage appears proper such Judge of the High Court or District`
  line `Judge, as the case may be, shall declare the marriage to be a proper marriage.`
  line
  line `Such declaration shall be as effectual as if the person whose consent was needed had consented to the`
  line marriage;
  line
  line `and, if he has forbidden the issue of the Marriage Registrar's certificate, such certificate shall be`
  line `issued and the like proceedings may be had under this Part in relation to the marriage as if the issue of`
  line `such certificate had not been forbidden.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (34013)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Petition when Marriage Registrar refuses certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34013&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a Marriage Registrar refuses`
  line `to issue a certificate under this Part, either of the parties intending marriage may apply by petition, where`
  line `the district of such Registrar is within any of the towns of Calcutta, Madras and Bombay, to a Judge of`
  line `the High Court, or if such district is not within any of the said towns, then to the District Judge.`
  line
  line `Procedure on petition.-- The said Judge of the High Court, or District Judge, as the case may be,`
  line `may examine the allegations of the petition in a summary way, and shall decide thereon.`
  line
  line `The decision of such Judge of the High Court or District Judge, as the case may be, shall be final, and`
  line `the Marriage Registrar to whom the application for the issue of a certificate was originally made shall`
  line `proceed in accordance therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (34014)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Petition when Marriage Registrar in Indian State refuses certificate.] Omitted by the A. O. 1950.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34014&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (34015)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Petition when Registrar doubts authority of person forbidding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Omitted by the A. O. 1950.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34015&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a Marriage`
  line `Registrar, acting under the provisions of section 44, is not satisfied that the person forbidding the issue of`
  line `the certificate is authorized by law so to do, the said Marriage Registrar shall apply by petition, where his`
  line `district is within any of the towns of Calcutta, Madras and Bombay, to a Judge of the High Court, or if`
  line `such district be not within any of the said towns, then to the District Judge.`
  line
  line `Procedure on petition.-- The said petition shall state all the circumstances of the case, and pray for`
  line `the order and direction of the Court concerning the same,`
  line
  line `and the said Judge of the High Court or District Judge, as the case may be, shall examine into the`
  line `allegations of the petition and the circumstances of the case,`
  line
  line `and if, upon such examination, it appears, that the person forbidding the issue of such certificate is not`
  line `authorized by law so to do, such Judge of the High Court or District Judge, as the case may be, shall`
  line `declare that the person forbidding the issue of such certificate is not authorized as aforesaid,`
  line
  line `and thereupon such certificate shall be issued, and the like proceedings may be had in relation to such`
  line `marriage as if the issue had not been forbidden.`
  line
  line ^1*****
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (34016)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Liability for frivolous protest against issue of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34016&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Every person entering a protest with`
  line `the Marriage Registrar, under this Part, against the issue of any certificate, on grounds which such`
  line `Marriage Registrar, under section 44, or a Judge of the High Court or the District Judge, under section 45`
  line `or 46, declares to be frivolous and such as ought not to obstruct the issue of the certificate, shall be liable`
  line `for the costs of all proceedings in relation thereto and for damages, to be recovered by suit by the person`
  line `against whose marriage such protest was entered.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (34017)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Form of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34017&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The certificate to be issued by the Marriage Registrar under the provisions`
  line `of section 41 shall be in the form contained in the Second Schedule to this Act annexed or to the like`
  line effect,
  line
  line `and the State Government shall furnish to every Marriage Registrar a sufficient number of forms of`
  line certificate.
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (34018)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Solemnization of marriage after issue of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34018&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `After the issue of the certificate of the`
  line `Marriage Registrar, or, where notice is required to be given under this Act to the Marriage Registrars for`
  line `different districts, after the issue of the certificates of the Marriage Registrars for such districts,`
  line
  line `marriage may, if there be no lawful impediment to the marriage of the parties described in such`
  line `certificate or certificates, be solemnized between them, according to such form and ceremony as they`
  line `think fit to adopt.`
  line
  line `But every such marriage shall be solemnized in the presence of some Marriage Registrar (to whom`
  line `shall be delivered such certificate or certificates as aforesaid), and of two or more credible witnesses`
  line `besides the Marriage Registrar:`
  line
  line `And in some part of the ceremony each of the parties shall declare as follows, or to the like effect:—`
  line
  line `"I do solemnly declare that I know not of any lawful impediment why I, A. B., may not be joined in`
  line `matrimony to C. D."`
  line
  line `And each of the parties shall say to the other as follows or to the like effect:—`
  line
  line `"I call upon these persons here present to witness that I, A. B., do take thee, C. D., to be my lawful`
  line `wedded wife [or husband.]."`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (34019)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `When marriage not had within two months after notice, new notice required.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34019&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a`
  line `marriage is not solemnized within two months after the copy of the notice has been entered by the`
  line `Marriage Registrar, as required by section 40, the notice and the certificate, if any, issued thereupon, and`
  line `all other proceedings thereupon, shall be void;`
  line
  line `and no person shall proceed to solemnize the marriage, nor shall any Marriage Registrar enter the`
  line `same, until new notice has been given, and entry made, and certificate thereof given, at the time and in the`
  line `manner aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (34020)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Marriage Registrar may ask for particulars to be registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34020&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `A Marriage Registrar before`
  line `whom any marriage is solemnized under this Part may ask of the persons to be married the several`
  line `particulars required to be registered touching such marriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (34021)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Registration of marriages solemnized under part V.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34021&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `After the solemnization of any marriage`
  line `under this Part, the Marriage Registrar present at such solemnization shall forthwith register the marriage`
  line `in duplicate; that is to say, in a marriage-register-book, according to the form of the Fourth Schedule`
  line `hereto annexed, and also in a certificate attached to the marriage-register-book as a counterfoil.`
  line
  line `The entry of such marriage in both the certificates and the marriage-register-book shall be signed by`
  line `the person by or before whom the marriage has been solemnized, if there be any such person, and by the`
  line `Marriage Registrar present at such marriage, whether or not it is solemnized by him, and also by the`
  line `parties married, and attested by two credible witnesses other than the Marriage Registrar and person`
  line `solemnizing the marriage.`
  line
  line `Every such entry shall be made in order from the beginning to the end of the book, and the number of`
  line `the certificate shall correspond with that of the entry in the marriage-register-book.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (34022)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Certificates to be sent monthly to Registrar General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30, for "Secretary to the Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34022&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The Marriage Registrar shall forthwith`
  line `separate the certificate from the marriage-register-book and send it, at the end of every month, to the`
  line `^1[Registrar General of Births, Deaths and Marriages].`
  line
  line `Custody of register-book.The Marriage Registrar shall keep safely the said register-book until it is`
  line `filled, and shall then send it to the ^1[Registrar General of Births, Deaths and Marriages], to be kept by him`
  line `with the records of his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (34023)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Officers to whom Registrars in Indian States shall send certificates.] Omitted by the A. O. 1950`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34023&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (34024)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Registrars to ascertain that notice and certificate are understood by Indian Christians.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "Native Christians".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34024&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `When any ^1[Indian Christians] about to be married gives a notice of marriage, or applies for a certificate`
  line `from a Marriage Registrar, such Marriage Registrar shall as certain whether the said ^1`
  line `[Indian Christians]`
  line `understands the English language, and, if he does not, the Marriage Registrar shall translate, or cause to`
  line `be translated, such notice or certificate, or both of them, as the case may be, to such ^1`
  line `[Indian Christians]`
  line `into a language which he understands;`
  line
  line `or the Marriage Registrar shall otherwise ascertain whether the`
  line ^1[
  line `Indian Christians] is cognizant of`
  line `the purport and effect of the said notice and certificate.`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (34025)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Indian Christians to be made to understand declarations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "Native Christians".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34025&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `When any ^1[Indian Christians] is`
  line `married under the provisions of this Part, the person solemnizing the marriage shall ascertain whether`
  line `such ^1[Indian Christians] understands the English language, and, if he does not, the person solemnizing`
  line `the marriage shall, at the time of the solemnization, translate, or cause to be translated, to such ^1[Indian`
  line `Christians], into a language which he understands, the declarations made at such marriage in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (34026)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Registration of marriages between Indian Christians.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "Native Christians".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34026&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The registration of marriages between`
  line `^1[Indian Christians] under this Part shall be made in conformity with the rules laid down in section 37`
  line `(so far as they are applicable), and not otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (34027)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `On what conditions marriages of Indian Christians may be certified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34027&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `^1, On what conditions marriages of ^1[Indian Christians] may be certified.--Every marriage`
  line `between ^1[Indian Christians] applying for a certificate, shall, without the preliminary notice required`
  line `under Part III, be certified under this Part, if the following conditions be fulfilled, and not otherwise:`
  line
  line `(1) the age of the man intending to be a married ^2[shall not be under ^3[twenty-one years]], and the age`
  line `of the woman intending to be married ^4[shall not be under ^5[eighteen years]];`
  line
  line `(2) neither of the persons intending to be married shall have a wife or husband still living;`
  line
  line `(3) in the presence of a person licensed under section 9, and of at least two credible witnesses other`
  line `than such person, each of the parties shall say to the other--`
  line
  line `"I call upon these persons here present to witness that. 1, A. B., in the presence of Almighty God,`
  line `and in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, do take thee, C. D., to be my lawful wedded wife`
  line `[or husband]" or words to the like effect:`
  line
  line ^6*****
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Act A.O. 1950, for "Native Christians"`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 48 of 1952, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "shall exceed sixteen years".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 2 of 1978, s. 6 and the Schedule, for "eighteen years" (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 48 of 1952, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "shall exceed thirteen years".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 2 of 1978, s. 6 and Schedule, for "fifteen years" (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
  line
  line `6. Proviso omitted by s. 6 and the Schedule, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-10-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (34028)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Grant of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34028&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `When, in respect to any marriage solemnized under this Part, the`
  line `conditions prescribed in section 60 have been fulfilled, the person licensed as aforesaid, in whose`
  line `presence the said declaration has been made, shall, on the application of either of the parties to such`
  line `marriage, and, on the payment of a fee of four annas, grant a certificate of the marriage.`
  line
  line `The certificate shall be signed by such licensed person, and shall be received in any suit touching the`
  line `validity of such marriage as conclusive proof of its having been performed.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (34029)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Keeping of register-book and deposit of extracts therefrom with Registrar General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34029&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `^1[62. Keeping of register-book and deposit of extracts therefrom with Registrar`
  line `General.-- (1) Every person licensed under section 9 shall keep in English, or in the vernacular language`
  line `in ordinary use in the district or State in which the marriage was solemnized, and in such form as the State`
  line `Government by which he was licensed may from time to time prescribe, a register-book of all marriages`
  line `solemnized under this Part in his presence, and shall deposit in the office of the Registrar General of`
  line `Births, Deaths and Marriages for the territories under the administration of the said State Government, in`
  line `such form and at such intervals as that Government may prescribe, true and duly authenticated extracts`
  line `from his register-book of all entries made therein since the last of those intervals.]`
  line
  line `^2** * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1891, s. 4, for s. 62.`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (34030)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Searches in register-book and copies of entries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34030&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Every person licensed under this Act to grant`
  line `certificates of marriage, and keeping a marriage-register-book under section 62, shall at all reasonable`
  line `times, allow search to be made in such book, and shall, on payment of the proper fee, give a copy,`
  line `certified under his hand, of any entry therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (34031)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Books in which marriages Indian Christians under Part I or Part III are registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34031&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of sections 62 and 63, as to the form of the of register-book, depositing extracts therefrom, allowing searches thereof, and giving copies of the entries therein, shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to the`
  line `books kept under section 37.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (34032)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Part VI not to apply to Roman Catholics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34032&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Saving of certain marriages.--This Part of this Act, except so much of sections 62 and 63 as are`
  line `referred to in section 64, shall not apply to marriages between Roman Catholics. But nothing herein`
  line `contained shall invalidate any marriage celebrated between Roman Catholics under the provisions of Part`
  line `V of Act No. 25 of 1864, previous to the twenty-third day of February, 1865.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (34033)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `False oath, declaration, notice or certificate for procuring marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1891, s. 5, for s. 66.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34033&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `^1[66. False oath, declaration, notice or certificate for procuring marriage.-- Whoever, for the`
  line `purpose of procuring a marriage or licence of marriage, intentionally,`
  line
  line `(a) where an oath or declaration is required by this Act, or by any rule or custom of a Church`
  line `according to the rites and ceremonies of which a marriage is intended to be solemnized, such Church`
  line `being the Church of England or of Scotland or of Rome, makes a false oath or declaration, or,`
  line
  line `(b) where a notice or certificate is required by this Act, signs a false notice or certificate,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have committed the offence punishable under section 193 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years and, at`
  line `the discretion of the Court, with fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (34034)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Forbidding, by false personation issue of certificate by Marriage Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34034&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `forbids the issue, by a Marriage Registrar, of a certificate, by falsely representing himself to be a person`
  line `whose consent to the marriage is required by law, knowing or believing such representation to be false, or`
  line `not having reason to believe it to be true, shall be deemed guilty of the offence described in section 205 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (34035)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Solemnizing marriage without due authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34035&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `^1[68. Solemnizing marriage without due authority. -- Whoever, not being authorized by section 5 of`
  line `of this Act to solemnize marriages, solemnizes or professes to solemnize, in the absence of a Marriage`
  line `Registrar of the district in which the ceremony takes place, a marriage between persons one or both of`
  line `whom is or are a Christian or Christians, shall be punished with imprisonment which may extend to ten`
  line `years, or (in lieu of a sentence of imprisonment for seven years or upwards) with transportation for a term`
  line `of not less than seven years, and not exceeding ten years,`
  line
  line ^2*****
  line
  line `and shall also be liable to fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for s. 68.`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (34036)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Solemnizing marriage out of proper time, or without witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1891, s. 7.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34036&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly and`
  line `wilfully solemnizes a marriage between persons, one or both of whom is or are a Christian or Christians,`
  line `at any time other than between the hours of six in the morning and seven in the evening, or in the absence`
  line `of at least two credible witnesses other than the person solemnizing the marriage, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Saving of marriages solemnized under special licence.-- This section does not apply to marriages`
  line `solemnized under special licences granted by the Anglican Bishop of the Diocese or by his Commissary,`
  line `nor to marriages performed between the hours of seven in the evening and six in the morning by a`
  line `Clergyman of the Church of Rome, when he has received the general or special license in that behalf`
  line `mentioned in section 10.`
  line
  line `^1[Nor does this section apply to marriages solemnized by a Clergyman of the Church of Scotland`
  line `according to the rules, rites, ceremonies and customs of the Church of Scotland.]`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (34037)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Solemnizing without notice or within fourteen days after notice, marriage with minor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34037&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `Minister of Religion licensed to solemnize marriages under this Act, who, without a notice in writing, or,`
  line `when one of the parties to the marriage is a minor and the required consent of the parents or guardians to`
  line `such marriage has not been obtained, within fourteen days after the receipt by him of notice of such`
  line `marriage, knowingly and wilfully solemnizes a marriage under Part III, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (34038)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Issuing certificate, or marrying, without publication of notice; Marrying after expiry of notice; Solemnizing, marriage with minor within fourteen days, without authority of Court, or without sending copy of notice; issuing certificate against authorized prohibition`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1891, s. 8(1), for clause (2).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34038&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `A Marriage Registrar under`
  line `this Act, who commits any of the following offences:--`
  line
  line `(1) knowingly and wilfully issues any certificate for marriage, or solemnizes any marriage, without`
  line `publishing the notice of such marriage as directed by this Act;`
  line
  line `^1[(2)marrying after expiry of notice.-- after the expiration of two months after the copy of the`
  line `notice has been entered as required by section 40 in respect of any marriage, solemnizes such marriage;]`
  line
  line `(3) solemnizing marriage with minor within fourteen days, without authority of Court, or`
  line `without sending copy of notice.-- solemnizes, without an order of a competent Court authorizing him to`
  line `do so, any marriage, when one of the parties is a minor, before the expiration of fourteen days after the`
  line `receipt of the notice of such marriage, or without sending, by the post or otherwise, a copy of such notice`
  line `to the Senior Marriage Registrar of the district if there be more Marriage Registrars of the district than`
  line `one, and if he himself be not the Senior Marriage Registrar;`
  line
  line `(4) issuing certificate against authorized prohibition.-- issues any certificate the issue of which has`
  line `been prohibited, as in this Act provided, by any person authorized to prohibit the issue thereof,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (34054)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Issuing certificate after expiry of notice, or, in case of minor, within fourteen days after notice, or against authorized prohibition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8(2), ibid., for "three months".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34054&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Any Marriage Registrar knowingly and wilfully issuing any`
  line `certificate for marriage after the expiration of ^1[`
  line `two months] after the notice has been entered by him as`
  line aforesaid,
  line
  line `fourteen days after notice, or against authorized prohibition.-- or knowingly and wilfully issuing,`
  line `without the order of a competent Court authorizing him so to do, any certificate for marriage, where one`
  line `of the parties intending marriage is a minor, before the expiration of fourteen days after the entry of such`
  line `notice, or any certificate the issue of which has been forbidden as aforesaid by any person authorized in`
  line `this behalf,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have committed an offence under section 166 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (34055)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Persons authorized to solemnize marriage (other than Clergy of Churches of England, Scotland or Rome); issuing certificate, or marrying, without publishing notice, or after expiry of certificate; issuing certificate for, or solemnizing, marriage with minor, within fourteen days after notice; issuing certificate authorizedly forbidden; solemnizing marriage authorizedly forbidden;`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34055&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being authorized under this Act to solemnize a marriage,`
  line
  line `and not being a Clergyman of the Church of England solemnizing a marriage after due publication of`
  line `banns, or under a license from the Anglican Bishop of the Diocese or a Surrogate duly authorized in that`
  line behalf,
  line
  line `or, not being a Clergyman of the Church of Scotland, solemnizing a marriage according to the rules,`
  line `rites, ceremonies and customs of that church,`
  line
  line `or, not being a Clergyman of the Church of Rome, solemnizing a marriage according to the rites,`
  line `rules, ceremonies and customs of that church,`
  line
  line `issuing certificate, or marrying, without publishing notice or after expiry of`
  line `certificate;-- knowingly and wilfully issues any certificate for marriage under this Act, or solemnizes any`
  line `marriage between such persons as aforesaid, without publishing, or causing to be affixed, the notice of`
  line `such marriage as directed in Part III of this Act, or after the expiration of two months after the certificate`
  line `has been issued by him;`
  line
  line `issuing certificate for, or solemnizing, marriage with minor, within fourteen days after`
  line `notice.-- or knowingly and wilfully issues any certificate for marriage, or solemnizes a marriage between`
  line `such persons when one of the persons intending marriage is a minor, before the expiration of fourteen`
  line `days after the receipt of notice of such marriage, or without sending, by the post or otherwise, a copy of`
  line `such notice to the Marriage Registrar, or, if there be more Marriage Registrars than one, to the Senior`
  line `Marriage Registrar of the district;`
  line
  line `issuing certificate authorizedly forbidden.-- or knowingly and wilfully issues any certificate the`
  line `issue of which has been forbidden, under this Act, by any person authorized to forbid the issue;`
  line
  line `solemnizing marriage authorizedly forbidden.-- or knowingly and wilfully solemnizes any`
  line `marriage forbidden by any person authorized to forbid the same;`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to four years, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (34056)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Unlicensed person granting certificate pretending to be licensed`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1891, s. 9.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34056&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, not being`
  line `licensed to grant a certificate of marriage under Part VI of this Act, grants such certificate intending`
  line `thereby to make it appear that he is so licensed, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to five years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `^1[Whoever, being licensed to grant certificates of marriage under Part VI of this Act, without just`
  line `cause refuses, or wilfully neglects or omits, to perform any of the duties imposed upon him by that Part`
  line `shall be punished with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (34057)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Destroying or falsifying register-books`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34057&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, by himself or another, wilfully destroys or`
  line `injures any register-book or the counterfoil certificates thereof, or any part thereof, or any authenticated`
  line `extract therefrom,`
  line
  line `or falsely makes or counterfeits any part of such register-book or counterfoil certificates,`
  line
  line `or wilfully inserts any false entry in any such register-book or counterfoil certificate or authenticated`
  line extract,
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (34058)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Limitation of prosecutions under Act`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34058&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `The prosecution for every offence punishable under`
  line `this Act shall be commenced within two years after the offence is committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (34059)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `What matters need not be proved in respect of marriage in accordance with Act`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34059&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line Whenever
  line `any marriage has been solemnized in accordance with the provisions of sections 4 and 5, it shall not be`
  line `void merely on account of any irregularity in respect of any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) any statement made in regard to the dwelling of the persons married, or to the consent of any`
  line `person whose consent to such marriage is required by law;`
  line
  line `(2) the notice of the marriage;`
  line
  line `(3) the certificate or translation thereof;`
  line
  line `(4) the time and place at which the marriage has been solemnized;`
  line
  line `(5) the registration of the marriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (34060)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Corrections of errors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30, for "Secretary to a Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34060&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Every person charged with the duty of registering any marriage, who`
  line `discovers any error in the form or substance of any such entry, may within one month next after the`
  line `discovery of such error, in the presence of the persons married, or, in case of their death or absence, in the`
  line `presence of two other credible witnesses, correct the error by entry in the margin, without any alteration`
  line `of the original entry, and shall sign the marginal entry, and add thereto the date of such correction, and`
  line `such person shall make the like marginal entry in the certificate thereof.`
  line
  line `And every entry made under this section shall be attested by the witnesses in whose presence it was`
  line made.
  line
  line `And, in case such certificate has been already sent to the ^1[Registrar General of Births, Deaths and`
  line `Marriages], such person shall make and send in like manner a separate certificate of the original`
  line `erroneous entry, and of the marginal correction therein made.`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (34061)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Searches and copies of entries`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1886, s. 30, for "Secretary to a Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34061&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `Every person solemnizing a marriage under this Act, and`
  line `hereby required to register the same,`
  line
  line `and every Marriage Registrar or ^1[Registrar General of Births, Deaths and Marriages] having the`
  line `custody for the time being of any register of marriages, or of any certificate, or duplicate, or copies of`
  line `certificate, under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall, on payment of the proper fees, at all reasonable times, allow searches to be made in such register, or`
  line `for such certificate, or duplicate or copies, and give a copy under his hand of any entry in the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (34062)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Certified copy of entry in marriage register, etc., to be evidence`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34062&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `Every certified copy,`
  line `purporting to be signed by the person entrusted under this Act with the custody of any marriage-register`
  line `or certificate, or duplicate, required to be kept or delivered under this Act, of any entry of a marriage in`
  line `such register or of any such certificate or duplicate, shall be received as evidence of the marriage`
  line `purporting to be so entered, or of the facts purporting to be so certified therein, without further proof of`
  line `such register or certificate, or duplicate, or of any entry therein, respectively, or of such copy.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (34063)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Certificates of certain marriages to be sent to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34063&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `^1[81. Certificates of certain marriages to be sent to Central Government.--The Registrar General`
  line `of Births, Deaths and Marriages ^2*** shall, at the end of every quarter in each year, select, from the`
  line `certificates of marriages forwarded to ^3[`
  line `him], during such quarter, the certificates of the marriages of`
  line `which ^4[the Government by whom he was appointed] may desire that evidence shall be transmitted to`
  line `England, and shall send the same certificates, signed by ^3[him] to the ^5`
  line `[Central Government].]`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 1911, s. 2, for s. 81.`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures "and the officers appointed under section 56" omitted by Act 48 of 1952, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid., for "them respectively".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the G. G. in C.".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Secretary of State for India".`
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (34064)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `State Government to prescribe fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34064&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Fees shall be chargeable under this Act for--`
  line
  line `receiving and publishing notices of marriages;`
  line
  line `issuing ^1[certificates for marriage] by Marriage Registrars, and registering marriages by the same;`
  line
  line `entering protests against, or prohibitions of, the issue of ^2[certificates for marriage] by the said`
  line Registrars;
  line
  line `searching register-books or certificates, or duplicates, of copies thereof;`
  line
  line `giving copies of entries in the same under sections 63 and 79.`
  line
  line `The State Government shall fix the amount of such fees respectively,`
  line
  line `and may from time to time vary or remit them either generally or in special cases, as to it may seem`
  line fit.
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1903, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "certificates of marriage".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid., for "marriage certificates".`
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (34065)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Power to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34065&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) ]The State Government ^2 [may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules] in regard to the disposal of the fees mentioned in section 82, the supply of`
  line `register-books, and the preparation and submission of returns of marriages solemnized under this Act.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 83 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid., for "may make rules" (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (34066)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title Omitted..
  content `[Power to prescribe fees and rules for Indian States.] Omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34066&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (34067)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to declare who shall be District Judge`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34067&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, declare who shall, in any place to which this Act applies, be deemed to be the`
  line `District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (34068)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title Omitted.
  content `[Powers and functions exercisable as regards Indian States.] Omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34068&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (34069)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Saving of Consular marriages`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34069&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act applies to any marriage performed by any`
  line `Minister, Consul, or Consular Agent between subjects of the State which he represents and according to`
  line `the laws of such State.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (34070)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Non-validation of marriages within prohibited degrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126&sectionId=34070&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00036_187215_1523269135126
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall be deemed`
  line `to validate any marriage which the personal law applicable to either of the parties forbids him or her to`
  line `enter into.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
